{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0adc8b0-bece-421c-83b9-eb4bdeff7281","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. Since this is a general question rather than a repo-specific task, here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Configure NuGet.org trusted publishing\nOn **nuget.org**, go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted Publishers** and register your GitHub repository (owner, repo, optionally branch/environment).\n\n### 2. Update your workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After (OIDC):**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n  contents: read\n\nsteps:\n  - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n  - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n    with:\n      dotnet-version: '8.0.x'\n\n  - run: dotnet build --configuration Release\n  - run: dotnet pack --configuration Release\n\n  - name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n    run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n    env:\n      NUGET_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}  # not needed if dotnet CLI ≥ 8.0.4xx\n```\n\n### Key changes\n1. **Add `id-token: write` permission** — lets the runner request an OIDC token.\n2. **Remove `--api-key`** — the CLI authenticates via the OIDC token instead.\n3. **Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret** — no longer needed.\n4. **Register your repo on nuget.org** as a trusted publisher.\n\nWith `dotnet` SDK **≥ 8.0.4xx**, the CLI auto-detects GitHub Actions and exchanges the OIDC token for NuGet auth — no extra action or secret needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88504687-4675-4e09-bdaf-a70cdaf5425e","outputTokens":490,"requestId":"C818:31347C:AC5A2:D73BC:69F54B20"},"id":"2e10d290-f9d0-4da7-9bf0-26d55d9666d3","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:54:02.328Z","parentId":"a41b7467-dd7d-4960-aa62-ddc95d54af40"}
